    <p class="govuk-body">To reset devices, you need to access the device BIOS and reset the password.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body">When youâ€™ve completed this stage, remember to work through the rest of the guidance to the end.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      How to access the BIOS for your device
    </h3>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If your specific device is not listed below, follow the
      <%= govuk_link_to 'instructions for other makes and models', '#other-makes-models' %>.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you have any issues during this process, take screenshots of the stage(s) you&rsquo;re unable
      to complete and
      <%= govuk_link_to 'contact us', support_ticket_path %>
      for technical support.
    </p>

    <%= render GovukComponent::AccordionComponent.new do |component| %>
      <%= component.section(heading_text: "Acer (all models)") do %>
        <%- begin %>

          <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Access BIOS
          </h4>

          <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>From the Windows Start menu, select the power icon</li>
            <li>Hold down &lsquo;Shift&rsquo; and select &lsquo;Restart&rsquo;</li>
            <li>When the &lsquo;Choose an option&rsquo; screen appears, select &lsquo;Troubleshoot&rsquo;</li>
            <li>On the &lsquo;Advanced Options&rsquo; screen, select &lsquo;UEFI Firmware settings&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Select &lsquo;Restart&rsquo;</li>
            <li>The device will boot into BIOS</li>
          </ol>

          <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Reset BIOS Password
          </h4>

          <p class="govuk-body">
            Check if your organisation has security policies that you need to follow before resetting
            and storing your passwords.
          </p>

          <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Enter the BIOS password (case sensitive)</li>
            <li>Select the &lsquo;Security&rsquo; tab and &lsquo;Set Supervisor Password&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Enter the current BIOS password when asked</li>
            <li>Enter and confirm your new password, or leave this blank</li>
            <li>Press &lsquo;Enter&rsquo; and when you see &lsquo;Changes have been saved&rsquo;, select &lsquo;Continue&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Press F10 to save and exit &ndash; confirm by selecting &lsquo;Yes&rsquo;</li>
          </ol>

        <%- end %>
      <% end %>
